### **Part II** &nbsp;&nbsp;Artifact Classification
> Place an **X** in the box that best describes this contribution.

- [ ] **asset**: New centralized image, diagram, or attachment.
- [ ] **chore**: Routine maintenance tasks such as dependency updates, formating changes, tweaks, or repository setup/cleanup.
- [ ] **governance**: Governance-related documents, such as the Architecture Operating Model (AOM), procedures, or meeting minutes.
- [ ] **library**: Reusable standards including design patterns, reference architectures, or glossary definitions.
- [ ] **templates**: New or updated document structures, boilerplate, or partials.
- [ ] **other**: Any change that does not fit the categories above.


> **Impact Level:**
- [ ] **Baseline Update** (New content/standard)
- [ ] **Revision** (Correction or minor update to existing content)
- [ ] **Superseded** (This PR renders a previous decision/pattern obsolete)


### **Part III** &nbsp;&nbsp;Governance & Quality Review
> Review and check each item to ensure repository integrity.

- [ ] **Technical/Accuracy** Content is factually correct to the best of your knowledge and aligns with current architectural principals.
- [ ] **Spelling/Grammar** Remediate spelling and grammar mistakes.
- [ ] **Link Integrity** All internal references and external links are functional.
- [ ] **No Sensitive Data** Verified that no secrets, credentials, or restricted internal data has been introduced.
